title: Titans rule Mariota out vs. Falcons, Mettenberger to start
text:
James Kenney Titans rule Mariota out vs. Falcons, Mettenberger to start 
Tennessee Titans quarterback Marcus Mariota (8) walks off the field with head coach Ken Whisenhunt after Mariota was injured in the first half of an NFL football game against the Miami Dolphins Sunday, Oct. 18, 2015, in Nashville, Tenn. (AP Photo/James Kenney) Posted: Friday, October 23, 2015 11:57 am | Updated: 4:01 pm, Fri Oct 23, 2015. Titans rule Mariota out vs. Falcons, Mettenberger to start Associated Press | 
NASHVILLE, Tenn. (AP) — Tennessee Titans rookie Marcus Mariota will not play Sunday against Atlanta as he recovers from a sprained MCL in his left knee. Zach Mettenberger will start at quarterback. 
Coach Ken Whisenhunt said Friday that Mariota has been ruled out after missing practice all week and the rookie's knee has not quite healed up.
